{
  "texts": [
    "As mentioned in (2), dataset aggregation, behavior cloning, inverse reinforcement learning, soft Q-learning, inverse Q-learning, self-imitation and transcendence, and others represent the field of hopefully eventually efficient R&D of ML in AECO.",
    "Second, training datasets -predicted open source platforms pose questions on materials assembly, materials quality, and size.",
    "A pragmatic optimization of the involved parameters structure appears a key task.",
    "The question of the data format with which the algorithm will work is crucial: it seems obvious that it should be one of the BIM formats.",
    "The basis of the algorithm structure could be -it seems -a pair of mutually interfering loops: a generative loop and an advice-whispering loop, or there can be more advice-whispering loops particularized according to the diverse natures of the parameters, which will be \"switched-on\" only in a cascade."
  ]
}